<task id="055" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Action Template — "Find similar matters" (Hybrid: Azure AI Search semantic + Deterministic Dataverse hydration)</title>
    <phase>Phase 5: Surfaces + Templates</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>040, 041, 052, 016</dependencies>
    <blocks>060</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, ai, azure-search, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>JPS Action JSON authoring + Dataverse seed for the "Conservative 3" Template #3 per spec.md FR-21. Wires the Hybrid invocation pattern (semantic search via Azure AI Search + deterministic Dataverse hydration). No new C# code; deliverable is JPS-validated JSON + AI Search index reference + deploy invocation. Has explicit ADR constraints (013, 015, 018) and dependencies on the AI Search index from task 016.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>E</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent JPS JSON authoring; writes to `infra/insights/schemas/template-find-similar-matters.json` — no file overlap with tasks 053, 054. Same prerequisite set (040 + 041 + 052) plus task 016 (AI Search index for Tool Registry — semantic-search infrastructure is reusable for matter-summary similarity). Safe for parallel sub-agent execution.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Author the "Find similar matters" Action Template as a JPS-compliant JSON definition at `infra/insights/schemas/template-find-similar-matters.json` and seed it into Dataverse (`sprk_actiontemplate` entity). Per spec.md FR-21 + design.md "Conservative 3", this is a **Hybrid** Action: takes a Matter record id + optional similarity dimensions (practice area, counterparty type, amount range); (Step 1) semantic search via Azure AI Search over a matter-summary semantic index returns ranked candidate matter ids; (Step 2) Deterministic Dataverse hydration of the top results enriches each candidate with metadata; output is a ranked list with citations and similarity rationale. Output routes to SpaarkeAi chat with hyperlinks back to matter records. Validates via `jps-validate` skill before deployment.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke AI Template author with deep familiarity with the JPS Action format, Azure AI Search semantic-search invocation (the `SearchSemantic` Tool registered in task 023 or equivalent — verify the Tool id before authoring), the Tool Registry's `EvidenceRequired` runtime guard (design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #3), citation discipline (guardrail #7), and the default `Spaarke Assistant — General` playbook from task 052.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **JPS Action JSON** — `infra/insights/schemas/template-find-similar-matters.json` with `instruction`, `scopes` (sourceMatterId), `templateParams` (`similarityDimensions`, `topK`, `minConfidence`), `steps`:
       - Step 1: `SearchSemantic` Tool against the matter-summary semantic index (Azure AI Search; the index may be `spaarke-matter-summary-index` or piggyback on `spaarke-resource-registry-index` — verify with task 016 / AI-ARCHITECTURE.md)
       - Step 2: `QueryDataverse` Tool hydrates the top-K results with metadata (practice area, counterparty, amount, status, partner)
       - Step 3: optional AI `ExplainSimilarity` Tool composes a short rationale per match
       , `output` schema with ranked candidates + citations + similarity rationale, `governance.featureFlag` reference.
    2. **Dataverse seed** — upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row keyed by `sprk_name = 'find-similar-matters'`. Idempotent.
    3. **Verification** — invoke manually via BFF `/run` AND via SpaarkeAi conversational invocation. Confirm:
       - Search returns ranked candidates with confidence scores
       - Hydration enriches each with metadata
       - Output includes `sourceCitations` referring to the dev-environment matter records
       - Result renders in SpaarkeAi chat with hyperlinks to the candidate matter forms (Dataverse deep links)
       - `EvidenceRequired: true` on the optional `ExplainSimilarity` step is honored (dispatch carries the Step 1 + Step 2 outputs as evidence)

    Deliverable: the JSON file, a deploy log at `notes/deploys/055-template-find-similar-matters.md`, and a verification of both the manual `/run` AND conversational invocation paths.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Spec.md FR-21 mandates the "Find similar matters" Template. Design.md "Conservative 3" decision confirms it as MVP Template #3. This Template is the **Hybrid invocation** demonstrator: it combines a probabilistic search step (semantic AI Search) with a deterministic hydration step (Dataverse query), validating that the Tool Registry's `Classification: Hybrid` (vs `Deterministic` / `AI`) properly supports multi-classification orchestration.

      The matter-summary semantic index is referenced as a dependency. Task 016 created the `spaarke-resource-registry-index` for Tool Registry discovery; the matter-summary index is either a separate index on the same `spaarke-search-dev` service OR (more likely for MVP) piggybacks on the existing `spaarke-file-index` with a tenant-scoped filter over matter records. Verify via `docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md` + the task 016 deploy output BEFORE authoring this Template — the Tool id and index name must match what's actually deployed.

      Per spec.md FR-21 acceptance: "Invocation from a Matter form returns 3-5 ranked candidates with similarity rationale; results render in chat with hyperlinks back to matter records." Two invocation paths exercise this:
      - **Manual / explicit-path**: ribbon button on Matter form (task 051) → opens SpaarkeAi side pane with pre-populated `actionTemplateId=find-similar-matters` and `entityId={matter}` → user clicks "Run" in result tile
      - **Conversational**: SpaarkeAi chat → "Find matters similar to {matter name}" → `FindResources` → `find-similar-matters` Template → resolves params → runs

      Both paths invoke the SAME Template; the Tool Registry doesn't care about path (design.md §4.5.1 "All three paths share the same runtime, the same Tool Registry, ..."). This Template is the proof point for that claim.

      Per design.md §7.4.5 guardrail #7 (citation discipline): the output's `sourceCitations` array MUST include a citation for each candidate matter (the matter id + URL). The UI renders these as hyperlinks.

      Per ADR-018, governance block references `feature.actionEngine.template.findSimilarMatters`.

      Per ADR-015, every Tool dispatch this Template makes writes audit (Tier 2 hash + Tier 3 work history).
    </background>
