  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, dependencies (tasks 040 + 041 + 052 + 016) marked ✅ in `TASK-INDEX.md`. Verify the matter-summary semantic index exists in the dev `spaarke-search-dev` Azure AI Search service via `az search index show` or equivalent. If absent, halt and escalate.</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;` — especially spec.md FR-21, design.md §7.4.5 (citation discipline), `docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md` (search infrastructure layout), and task 016's deploy output to confirm the actual Tool id + index name.</step>
    <step order="2">Use the `jps-action-create` skill to scaffold the Template JSON. Populate:
      - `instruction`: brief LLM-facing description: "Find matters semantically similar to a given matter, optionally filtered by practice area, counterparty type, or amount range. Returns a ranked list with similarity rationale and hyperlinks to each matter record."
      - `scopes`: `[{name: "sourceMatterId", type: "guid", required: true, sourceHints: ["surface", "ask"]}]`
      - `templateParams`: `[{name: "similarityDimensions", type: "stringArray", values: ["practiceArea","counterpartyType","amountRange","status"], default: ["practiceArea","counterpartyType"]}, {name: "topK", type: "int", default: 5, min: 3, max: 10}, {name: "minConfidence", type: "float", default: 0.7}]`
      - `steps`:
        - Step 1: `{tool: "SearchSemantic", params: {indexName: "&lt;verified-index-name-from-task-016&gt;", queryFromRecord: "{sourceMatterId}", topK: "{topK}", minConfidence: "{minConfidence}", filterDimensions: "{similarityDimensions}"}}` — Hybrid (AI classification)
        - Step 2: `{tool: "QueryDataverse", params: {entity: "sprk_matter", ids: "{step1.output.candidateIds}", fields: ["sprk_name","sprk_practicearea","sprk_counterpartytype","sprk_amount","sprk_status","sprk_partner","sprk_pm"]}}` — Deterministic
        - Step 3 (optional): `{tool: "ExplainSimilarity", params: {sourceMatter: "{step2.output.sourceMatter}", candidates: "{step2.output.candidates}", dimensions: "{similarityDimensions}"}, evidenceRequired: true, optional: true}` — AI, requires evidence from Step 2
      - `output`: `{candidates: [{matterId, name, confidence, similarityRationale, citation: {url, recordId}}], queryEcho: string, totalCandidates: int}`
      - `governance.featureFlag`: `"feature.actionEngine.template.findSimilarMatters"`
      - `humanGate.required`: `false` (read-only Template)
    </step>
    <step order="3">Run `jps-validate` skill. Halt and fix on schema violations.</step>
    <step order="4">Deploy via `scripts/Seed-JpsActions.ps1` (or equivalent): upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row keyed by `sprk_name = 'find-similar-matters'`. Capture stdout/stderr.</step>
    <step order="5">**Manual `/run` verification** — invoke via BFF `/run` endpoint: POST `/api/actions/run` with `{templateId: 'find-similar-matters', parameters: {sourceMatterId: '&lt;dev-matter-guid&gt;', topK: 5}}`. Confirm:
      - Run record created with status `Completed`
      - Step 1 (SearchSemantic) audit row present; query hashed in Tier 2
      - Step 2 (QueryDataverse) audit row present
      - Step 3 (ExplainSimilarity, optional) audit row present IF the step ran (depends on Template's `optional` semantics — verify with task 041 orchestrator)
      - Output contains 3-5 candidates with `confidence ≥ 0.7`, populated metadata, `similarityRationale` strings, and `sourceCitations` with hyperlink URLs to each matter form
    </step>
    <step order="6">**Conversational invocation verification** — in SpaarkeAi chat (no-context landing), type "Find matters similar to {matter name}" using a real dev-environment matter name. Confirm:
      - Agent calls `FindResources("find similar matters")` → returns `find-similar-matters` Template with high confidence
      - Agent calls `GetResourceDetail` → returns parameter schema with `sourceMatterId` source hint of "surface" or "ask"
      - Agent resolves `sourceMatterId` via a `QueryDataverse` lookup by matter name (or asks the user to disambiguate if multiple match)
      - Agent calls `InvokeResource` → runs the Template
      - Output rendered in chat as a list with hyperlinks to candidate matter forms
    </step>
    <step order="7">**Explicit-path verification** (ribbon launcher from Matter form per task 051) — open a dev Matter, click "Open Spaarke AI" ribbon button, in the side pane invoke "Find similar matters" via the result tile (or via chat with entity context). Confirm the `sourceMatterId` is auto-populated from the surface context (no user input needed). Same output behavior as step 6.</step>
    <step order="8">**Idempotency verification**: re-run the seed script. Confirm record count = 1.</step>
    <step order="9">Capture all verification evidence in `notes/deploys/055-template-find-similar-matters.md`.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md`; checkpoint via `context-handoff`. Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 055 ✅. If deviations, document in `notes/handoffs/055-deviations.md`.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="jps-action-create">Scaffold the JPS Action JSON</tool>
    <tool name="jps-validate">Validate JSON against JPS schema</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Upsert `sprk_actiontemplate` row</tool>
    <tool name="powershell">Run Seed-JpsActions.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="curl">Invoke BFF `/run` endpoint for manual verification</tool>
    <tool name="azure-cli">Verify AI Search index existence + state</tool>
  </tools>

