    <output type="docs">projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/current-task.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`infra/insights/schemas/template-find-similar-matters.json` exists and passes `jps-validate`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template's Step 1 (`SearchSemantic`) references the actual matter-summary semantic index name verified against task 016's deploy output.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template's optional Step 3 (`ExplainSimilarity`) has `EvidenceRequired: true` referring to Step 2's output.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The Template's `governance.featureFlag` references `feature.actionEngine.template.findSimilarMatters`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After deployment, exactly one `sprk_actiontemplate` row with `sprk_name='find-similar-matters'` exists. Re-running the seed yields no duplicate.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Manual `/run` verification**: invocation returns 3-5 candidates with `confidence ≥ minConfidence`, hydrated metadata, and `sourceCitations` containing hyperlinks. Evidence in `notes/deploys/055-*.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Conversational verification**: SpaarkeAi chat "Find matters similar to {matter name}" resolves to this Template via `FindResources` and runs end-to-end. Evidence captured.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Explicit-path verification**: ribbon-launched side pane auto-populates `sourceMatterId` from surface context (no user input). Evidence captured.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Output schema's `sourceCitations` array is populated for every candidate; UI hyperlinks resolve to the candidate matter forms.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta zero.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The matter-summary semantic index may not exist as a standalone index in MVP. Verify with task 016's deploy notes:
      (a) If task 016 created `spaarke-resource-registry-index` AND a separate `spaarke-matter-summary-index`, use the matter-summary one.
      (b) If task 016 only created the Tool Registry index AND the matter-summary similarity reuses `spaarke-file-index` with a tenant + entityType filter, use that.
      (c) If neither exists, escalate — this Template's verification path is broken without the index.

    Per design.md §4.5.1: "The same Action ("Send weekly task digest to Smith Co") can be invoked all three ways". This Template is the proof point for the conversational + explicit paths (the system / scheduled path is exercised by task 054). Both invocation paths exercise the SAME Template definition.

    The `SearchSemantic` Tool id is referenced indirectly — verify the actual Tool name registered in task 023 / 022 (always-on tool registration) before authoring. If it's called `SemanticSearch` or `AzureSearchHybridQuery`, use that exact id. Mismatched Tool ids will fail dispatch.

    The `similarityRationale` text is generated by the optional Step 3 (`ExplainSimilarity` AI Tool). If Step 3 is skipped (no AI Tool available in dev), the output should fall back to a deterministic rationale like "Same practice area + same counterparty type" — verify the orchestrator (task 041) handles `optional: true` steps correctly.

    Per ADR-015 data governance: the search query text MUST be hashed in Tier 2 audit (not plaintext). Verify via the dispatch audit row that the query hash (not the query) appears in the persisted record.

    Per spec.md Success Criteria #2 (G2 gate): this Template ALSO exercises the conversational invocation path. Task 053 records the canonical G2 evidence (Summarize Matter X); this Template's evidence is supplementary — proof that G2 generalizes beyond a single Template.
  </notes>

